He suffered the devastating snap of his Achilles tendon in April during a game against the Golden State Warriors.But Kobe Bryant didn't let an injury ruin his evening as he stepped out with wife Vanessa in Beverly Hills on Thursday.The pair donned complementary evening wear to attend An Unforgettable Evening benefiting the Entertainment Industry Foundation's Women's Cancer Research Fund. Staying positive: Just three weeks after suffering a devastating injury to his Achilles tendon, Kobe Bryant appeared buoyant with wife Vanessa at a charity event in Beverly Hills
Kobe, 34, seemed in high spirits as he entered the event aided by a set of crutches and wearing a foot brace. The champion player has remained optimistic following what he called the most disappointing injury of his career 'by far.''I
know I can do this,' he said of his recovery. 'It's fueling me. It's fueling me. I can feel it already.'He further rallied on Facebook: 'Maybe this is how my book ends. Maybe Father Time has defeated me...Then again maybe not!' Complementary couple: The pair, married since 2001, donned matching formal wear for the occasion
And his continued positivity was evident as he entered the philanthropic gala on the arm of his beaming wife of 12 years.The basketball star looked debonair in a black tuxedo and patent leather dress shoes.Meanwhile, Vanessa, 30, looked the perfect counterpart to her husband in a black dress with a high-low hemline layered over a white collared shirt and finished with a tie.The mother of two added pointed black stilettos fastened at the ankles and a quilted clutch to complete her ensemble. Undeterred: Kobe has remained optimistic throughout his recovery, and seemed in high spirits as he entered the event with crutches and a foot brace
The pair joined a slew of celebrity couples at the event, including honorary chairs Tom Hanks and Rita Wilson and Steven Spielberg and Kate Capshaw.Comedienne Chelsea Handler hosted the star-studded evening, while Bruno Mars provided guests with musical entertainment.On Wednesday, Kobe had his stitches removed 17 days after undergoing surgery to repair the damaged tendon.The legendary Laker posted a photograph of the process to Instagram beside the simple caption: 'Stitches out! #progress.' Progress: The star player recently had his stitches removed 17 days after undergoing surgery to repair the snapped tendon Yet the injury is not the only struggle the NBA standout is currently facing.As TMZ reported on Friday, he's embroiled in a legal battle against his mother, Pamela, who is trying to sell a collection of the athlete's basketball memorabilia through Goldin Auctions.The goods in question include several of Kobe's jerseys dating back to his days as a high school player, trophies, varsity letters and uniform pieces.Pamela, who received a $450,000 advance from the auction house, claims her son gave her the loot five years ago, but Kobe disagrees.As a result of the dispute, Goldin Auctions has taken the matter to court to ask a judge to name Pamela the rightful owner of the items. Another hurdle: Kobe currently is embroiled in a legal battle against his mother, Pamela, pictured here with husband Joe Betrayal? Pamela is attempting to sell a collection of her son's basketball memorabilia through Goldin Auctions, but Kobe claims his mother does not own the items in question
